WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.040
Hey everyone, my name is Cecil and I'm here with my colleague Jay and we're from the Posit

00:00:12.040 --> 00:00:18.480
support team and today we're going to talk through a little bit about Posit Workbench

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:21.040
and SSL certificates.

00:00:21.040 --> 00:00:29.160
So in our case here we have an SSL certificate called Demosert which is in the Etsy RStudio

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:36.119
directory and as you can see the permissions here are read-only for the Ubuntu user and

00:00:36.119 --> 00:00:38.119
group.

00:00:38.119 --> 00:00:46.480
It's a good idea to change the ownership of this file to the RStudio-Server user or if

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:51.000
you're using a different service account to run Workbench it would need to be the service

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.080
account that you're using to run Workbench.

00:00:54.080 --> 00:00:57.200
By default it's RStudio-Server.

00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:03.820
So what we want to do here is change the ownership so that it conforms to that.

00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:11.400
So what we do is a change of ownership for the RStudio-Server user and the RStudio-Server

00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:16.959
group to the file that we're using for our SSL certificate.

00:01:16.959 --> 00:01:19.519
So hit enter there.

00:01:19.519 --> 00:01:25.160
What we also want to do is to make sure the permissions are set to 644.

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:32.919
So we can go ahead and run that command as well and then if we rerun the ls commit that

00:01:32.919 --> 00:01:38.620
we saw earlier we should see the correct values here.

00:01:38.620 --> 00:01:45.199
You can see that now the certificate file is using 644 permissions and it's owned by

00:01:45.199 --> 00:01:50.160
the RStudio-Server user and RStudio-Server group.

00:01:50.160 --> 00:01:57.680
So now the certificate is ready to be put into the configuration file of your PositWorkBench host.

